history.content: Not sure how much the course has changed now, but back in Fall 2018, I had joined the waitlist for ee16a the same week school started and after changing into a lab that had potential for open spots, I was able to get in. Maybe someone who took the course more recently can comment if things have changed, but I would assume you'd be fine to get in with phase 2 (or the new phase 1.5 that's happening). Just try to choose a lab section that's either open or doesn't have many waitlisted people

I am an incoming sophomore, intended L&S CS. I'm currently enrolled in summer session on EE16A but need to drop it and will be Phase 2 enrolling in the class for Fall.

Does anyone know how hard this will be, given that they like to reserve so many seats for freshman & transfers? If it's highly likely I won't get a spot, I will reconsider dropping the summer session. Any advice is appreciated. 

Edit: just heard back from an advisor that they think it's fine if I drop the summer course, since they prioritize enrollment for 1st and 2nd years.
